"Oh, the faiwy! She can do anything with me!" said Denfsov, and he unhooked his saber. He came out from behind the chairs, clasped his partner's hand firmly, threw back his head, and advanced his foot, waiting for the beat. Only on horse back and in the mazurka was Denfsov's short stature not noticeable and he looked the fine fellow he felt himself to be.
